Linus Hoard Walker, legal counsel of the United States organization of KLM Royal Dutch Airlines, died Wednesday in Norwalk (Conn.) Hospital. He was 65 years old and lived in Rowayton, Conn.

Mr. Walker was counsel for the Civil Aeronautics Board before joining KLM in 1946, after the start of its operation here. He was regarded as an authority on international aviation law. He graduated from Whitman College and received: a law degree from the University of Washington.

Surviving are his wife, Mary a son, Mark; a daughter, Mary, and two brothers, John and Dr. Philip Walker.